            I think the problem with Real Madrid is partially of the president and the fans. Real Madrid have some really tough to satisfy fans that want the team to play consistently good, score lots of goals, not concede, win, collect all the possible trophies, buy the best players and be recognized as the best team of the world by far. This is coming from me, being a Real Madrid fan for over 18 years. The damage started when we fired Vicente Del Bosque and continued when we sold Makelele instead of offering him a proper contract and recognizing his contribution to the team. That was the point that it all started to slowly go south. We really should be more patient with our players and our coaches, cheer for the team even when we are losing so that we give them confidence to give their all in the pitch. Look at Atletico, they really are the best example of how fans help boost the morale of the players.
